{
  "texts": [
    "The use of spatial Bayesian methods has grown in favor of overcoming SAC.",
    "Bayesian Spatial Autoregressive (BSAR) models and Bayesian Spatial Error (BSEM) models explicitly account for SAC by incorporating a spatial dependency term and a spatially structured error term, respectively, to capture indirect spatial effects and unexplained spatial variation 143.",
    "Recently, the popularity of autoregressive models for spatial modeling as a core method has slightly decreased, while classical ML and DL methods have been extensively employed for spatial modeling tasks.",
    "Consequently, various techniques have been developed to leverage SAC's influence effectively.",
    "The common approach is to incorporate SAC with the usage of autoregressive models during the stages of dataset preparation and variable selection."
  ]
}